Durban – Police are hunting a gang of armed robbers who held up a cash-in-transit security guard at shopping centre in Inanda, North of Durban. According to police, the security guard and his colleague were about to load the cash into an ATM on Tuesday when the gang of robbers swarmed them.  “As he was opening the ATM cubicle door with an electronic smart lock key he was approached by three unidentified suspects,” Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said.  “The suspects produced firearms and at gunpoint robbed him of a cash box and a firearm. The suspects fled the crime scene in an unknown direction. No arrests or recoveries. No injuries reported. A case of cash-in-transit was opened for investigation at Inanda SAPS,” she said.  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
